  "shortDescription": "A static stretch targeting the triceps and lats by flexing the elbow overhead while kneeling.",
  "instructions": "Kneel on the floor and reach one arm overhead, bending the elbow to let your hand touch your upper back. With the opposite hand, gently press on the bent elbow to increase the stretch.",
  "steps": [
    "Kneel on the floor or mat.",
    "Raise one arm overhead then bend the elbow so your hand touches your upper back.",
    "Use your other hand to gently push on the bent elbow.",
    "Hold the stretch.",
    "Switch arms and repeat."
  ],
